  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Public Information Campaign to Deter Potential Irregular Maritime Migration from Vietnam to Australia in 2021-22</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since 2014, IOM Viet Nam has been entrusted by the Government of Australia to deliver a public information campaign in key source locations across Viet Nam to inform potential irregular migrants of Australia&#x2019;s strict border protection policies and the risks and consequences of going there by boat. The project closely coordinates with local government agencies to make use of a wide range of communication methods and activities to deliver these key messages. Being capable of reaching tens of thousands of target audiences every year, the campaign kept the number of irregular maritime journeys at a minimum. In 2021, the project has been renewed for a seventh phase. The campaign shall build upon best practices and strong government partnerships established under previous phases to maximize the impacts of communication activities. On top of the awareness raising component, this phase will also build capacity of local authorities and community leaders to organize outreach events and conduct community meetings at grassroots levels. It is expected that a strategic combination of communication methods will effectively support positive behaviour change and ultimately contribute to deter irregular maritime migration from Viet Nam to Australia.</narrative>
  </description>
